{
  "stem": "10181.5",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 18.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we had to walk.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This time there were no trucks to take us.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had to walk all the way to Celle, which was very difficult because all those were sick.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we had this-- aside from some-- some of us having typhus, we had this-- you get this disease from hunger.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was called edema or something like that, but-- the-- the way your-- everything swells, you know-- your-- your your legs swell, and-- and your-- you know, your joints swell up, and-- and this is-- this comes from-- from malnutrition, from hunger.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we walked to the-- to the train.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And this is one-- one of the few-- I saw-- we were guarded by German soldiers.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I think they were soldiers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I don't think they were SS.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I'm not sure.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But one or two of the soldiers tried to help some of the smaller children-- because there were children and-- and-- and-- to-- to make it.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was one of those cattle wagons where we got on.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we were I don't know how many in a cattle wagon.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It was-- the door was closed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we traveled like that for about five days.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We stopped once or twice in the middle.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But once we were let out and once we went and once we-- we were at a town called Stendal, which was-- in-- and in the railroad station and was being bombed.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they moved us out just as we were being bombed.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that-- after five days-- five or six days-- the train finally stopped near the Elbe.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was near the Elbe, which I didn't know it at the time, but I know it was near Magdeburg.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was a little town, or a little village, called Hillersleben nearby.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
